
[1]stimulus

   STIMULUS, n. [L. This word may be formed on the root of stem, a shoot.]
   Literally, a goad; hence, something that rouses from languor; that
   which excites or increases action in the animal system, as a stimulus
   in medicine; or that which rouses the mind or spirits; as, the hope of
   gain is a powerful stimulus to labor and action.
